0-download-perl-dependencies.sh
  Fetch the dependencies with curl and copy them in the ./tmp directory.
1-build-perl-tree.sh
  Take the dependencies and build them offline. It generates a tarball with
  just the perl distribution.
2-merge-fusinv-with-perl-tree.sh
  Take the generated tarball, merge FusionInventory Agent files and create
  a final tarball

See: http://forge.fusioninventory.org/projects/fusioninventory-agent/wiki/How_to_install_the_package_factory
